-- Michael Downey Named Chief of Britain’s Lawn Tennis Association
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-09-24T09:41:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-24/michael-downey-named-chief-of-britain-s-lawn-tennis-association.html
Britain’s Lawn Tennis Association
named Michael Downey its new chief executive officer, the
organization said in a  statement .  Downey, 56, has spent the past nine years as president and
CEO of Tennis  Canada . He replaces Roger Draper, who will step
down at the end of September after seven years in charge of the
LTA, which organizes the sport in Britain.  “We set out to recruit a CEO with true success in
business, with exceptional leadership credentials and ideally
with significant knowledge of tennis,” LTA Chairman David
Gregson said. “Michael demonstrably fits the bill perfectly and
was the unanimous choice of our recruitment panel.”  Downey will start in his new position on Jan. 6, 2014, the
LTA said. He was a senior vice president of Molson Canada, that
country’s largest brewery, as well as a marketing executive with
the Toronto Raptors of the National Basketball Association and
the Toronto Maple Leafs of the  National Hockey League .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bob Bensch in London at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
